---
---

<div>
  <div class="text-center mb-12">
    <span class="eyebrow">Your delivery record</span>
    <h2 class="mt-5 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
      A track record of shipped work, not course completions
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg copy-muted max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      Every lab produces real artifacts — PRs with review history, meaningful commits, technical decisions you can walk someone through. Not a certificate. A delivery record.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto surface-card p-7 mb-6 text-left">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">What you'll walk out with</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm copy-muted">
      Concrete artifacts that prove you can operate on a team, not just write code:
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-sm copy-muted">
      <p>✓ GitHub repo history with meaningful commits</p>
      <p>✓ Pull request history with review iterations</p>
      <p>✓ Project README and technical documentation</p>
      <p>✓ Shipped feature log with decisions/tradeoffs</p>
      <p>✓ Debug notes and test evidence from lab tasks</p>
      <p>✓ Clear portfolio narrative for each project</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Interview preparation callout -->
  <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto surface-card p-8 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent-2)]">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0">
        <div class="text-3xl">💬</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">When you talk about your work:</h3>
        <p class="copy-muted italic mb-3">
          "I built this feature to solve [specific problem]. I chose [technology] because [tradeoffs]. I'd approach this differently now because I learned [lesson]."
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm copy-subtle">
          You'll have shipped code and decision-making experience to point to — not course completions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
